            "language_code": "en",
            "text": "Aquaria KLCC"
          }
        ]
      },
      "description": {
        "localized_texts": [
          {
            "language_code": "en",
            "text": "Discover the wonders of the underwater world at Aquaria KLCC, a world-class oceanarium located beneath the Kuala Lumpur Convention Centre, just steps away from the iconic Petronas Twin Towers. As one of the city's top attractions, Aquaria KLCC offers an immersive marine experience in the heart of Kuala Lumpur. Home to over 5,000 aquatic and land-bound creatures, the oceanarium showcases fascinating marine life from around the globe, including tiger sharks, stingrays, sea snakes, seahorses, jellyfish, and more. Interactive zones allow visitors to enjoy close-up encounters with selected species, making the visit both educational and exciting. One of the main highlights is the spectacular 90-meter underwater tunnel, where you can walk through a transparent glass walkway surrounded by sharks, rays, and other marine creatures swimming overhead. Don't miss the touch pool experience, where you can gently interact with starfish and sea cucumbers."
          }
        ]
      },
      "rating": {
        "average_value": 4.4,
        "rating_count": 32600
      },
      "product_features": [
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "One of the Top Five Aquariums in Asia: Aquaria KLCC is recognized as one of the top five aquariums in Asia."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Impressive Exhibits: Over 5,000 land and aquatic creature exhibits across about 60,000 sq ft."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Underwater Journey: Malaysia's long underwater tunnel featuring iconic Malaysian and other marine species."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_HIGHLIGHT",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Conservation Efforts: Aquaria KLCC supports solutions that help make our oceans healthier."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_INCLUSION",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Full-day admission to Aquaria KLCC (exhibit access per ticket type: peak/off-peak, local/tourist as purchased)."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_INCLUSION",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Evolution zone: red-bellied piranha. Touch pool: piranha, brown-banded bamboo shark and horseshoe crab. Jewels of the Jungle: Asian small-clawed otter, electric eel and tokay gecko. Shipwreck: red lionfish and reef stonefish. The Stream: otters. Station Aquarius: moon jelly and seahorse. Flooded Forest: arapaima and alligator gar. The Coastal: archerfish and giant mudskipper. Living Ocean: sand tiger shark, green sea turtle and giant moray eel. Weird and Wonderful: pinecone fish."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Operation hours: visit the official Aquaria KLCC website for updates. Usual guide: Mon–Fri 10:00 AM–8:00 PM; Sat–Sun 10:00 AM–7:00 PM."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Indoor attraction—no wet-weather restrictions. Casual wear recommended. Wheelchairs available for rental at Aquaria KLCC."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Tickets valid 180 days from purchase. Free for under 3; child 3–12; adult 13–59; senior 60+. Children under 13 must be with an adult. Stroller- and wheelchair-accessible; staff can assist guests with disabilities."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Check feeding schedules on site or online. Re-entry is not allowed after you leave. Present mobile or printed voucher at the ticketing counter. No vendor cancellation unless your sales channel states otherwise."
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Peak vs off-peak pricing follows Aquaria KLCC rules (often aligned with weekends and Malaysian public holidays). For 2026 holiday reference, see the official Malaysian calendar or Aquaria's peak schedule before you buy."
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
